  - q: "When is Chinese New Year?"
    a: "Chinese New Year falls on the second new moon after the winter solstice, between January 21 and February 20 on the Gregorian calendar. The date shifts yearly because of the lunisolar calendar system."
  - q: "How long does the Spring Festival last?"
    a: "The festival spans 15 days, from New Year's Day to the Lantern Festival on the 15th of the first lunar month. New Year's Eve and the first five days are the most intensely celebrated."
  - q: "What is the Nian beast?"
